div.div: Boku no Kokoro no Yabai Yatsu

Fascinated by murder and all things macabre, Kyoutarou daydreams of acting out his twisted fantasies on his unsuspecting classmates — but an encounter with Anna Yamada, the gorgeous class idol, lights a spark in the darkness of his heart. It’s a classic tale of an antisocial boy falling for a popular girl, but neither are who they appear to be at first glance. Will Kyoutarou and Anna defy their expectations of each other — and of themselves?
(Source: HIDIVE)
Comedy, Drama, Psychological, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural

After last season’s revelations, the Soma family moves forward, but the emotional chains that bind them are not easily broken. Unable to admit why she wants the cure, Tohru wrestles with the truth, aware that time is running out for someone close. And a secret still lurks that could break another’s heart. But hope is not lost—a clue to the curse is found. Could their imprisonment’s end be near? (Source: Funimation) Note: This season premiered on Funimation and AnimeLab on March 20, 2021. The Japanese broadcast started two weeks later on April 6, 2021.

Childhood friends who've been together forever since they were little. Although they've noticed their feelings for each other, they're too close to be honest. What links them is the "I love you game" they have been playing since they were little. The conclusion to their love has been entrusted to this petty game, where winning means making the other person feel embarrassed.
(Source: Shogakukan, translated)
The (former) Takagi-san and her daughter, Chi-chan, bring you this teasing home comedy. Is Dad going to make an appearance too?
